annotation.TEXT: This part looks tricky, but it's still not bad.
I cut it kind of close there, but I knew where the solid land was.
Ooh. Yeah, I'm definitely going to show this off. If you hit the side of this block while clinging to the rope, a glitch occurs that lets you climb just about anywhere!
Goal tape average so far: 1484 / 39 = 38.051 stars each.

Once the glitch is triggered, you can climb through the air like this. You can jump with the B button to unstick yourself, but the glitch will remain active and you can once again climb by pressing up.
Goal tape average so far: 1604 / 42 = 38.190 stars each.
And, it looks like we're done here.
That unlocked 4-B, without clearing away the rock that the level dot is on first for some reason. But, whatever. Now let's replay 4-A for the secret exit.

You've gotta be a little fast to reveal the vine here and then climb it, but it's actually not that hard. Also, the vine is only used to help you get this star coin (and protect you from the lava). It doesn't actually lead to a new area or anything.

So, what's the "sol and luna" reference? Also, why would I get a Zangoose instead of a Linoone from evolving Zigzagoon that way? Oh, and if "dash one" actually meant something besides 4-1, let me know.
NOOOooo...
Yeah, they're definitely getting tricky.
Or not. Shouldn't have jumped there.
Alright, somehow I got to midpoint without getting cut up.

Okay, now since raocow pulled this off, I will too. You can duck-jump into this nook, and then stand upright on the far right and the game will eventually shove you into the block. There's no practical use for this, and you risk losing the platform, but fortunately, the platform is a persistent sprite, and you do have some time to catch up to it.
Wall springboards that aren't attached to a wall. Sure, why not?
Wait, I want to duck-jump onto these.

Note: The first two votes here actually were made a few episodes ago, but the comment containing them was flagged as spam for some reason, and I wasn't notified of it, so I wasn't even aware of that comment for a while. Fortunately, they weren't votes for the next level for me to play at the time.
Argh! Why do the bottoms of upside-down saws seem to stretch farther than they appear?

Now, let's do this secret exit thing right. I wonder how you're supposed to even find this one normally (without using the climbing glitch, finding out about it from someone else, or looking in Lunar Magic)?
Bonus game average so far: 109 / 15 = 7.267 1♥Ps each.
And, another game of the bonus kind.
Whoa, what the?! Why did I just fall off there? Good thing I was holding the B button and had my cape and reacted quickly enough!
Bonus game average so far: 112 / 16 = 7 1♥Ps each.
Darn it! I thought I'd be low enough to dodge that.
With my cape, I can skip the horizontally moving saw.
BGM: Catrap (Game Boy) - Catboy's Theme
If you're on these rotating platforms at high tide, you'll have to keep jumping to the highest one, but it's not that tricky.
Let's try not to let my average fall below 7!
I am actually surprised I hit the goal tape at all there. It looked like I came in too low, but the game gave it to me, so that was nice.
Okay, there's midpoint, so I get a free embiggening. Also, there's a feather block conveniently just after it.
Okay, now note now this pillar here appears to be pointing up, while the other pillars in the level have been pointing down. Yeah, that's your secret exit hint.
Whoa, I think I just did a frame-perfect rope jump there by accident!
Now, things could be different this time, since I'm not opening the level with a cape like last time. Let's see how well I can handle this level starting off with no power ups.

Ah, but we're not quite there yet. First, we've gotta "A" across some saws. Have you ever tried doing this to clear the original game's Cheese Bridge Area without using a rope, Yoshi, or flying? Yeah, it's kind of like that, though I think this is a bit easier.
So, yeah. Stop that shell before it falls into the lava, and kick it up into the off screen turn block to make the P-switch fall down. Stomp the P-switch, then head to the left and enter the pipe.
Goal tape average so far: 1564 / 41 = 38.146 stars each.
And that unlocks a path straight to world 7-1! Interesting... Now, which level should I start off with next time? Will it be 7-1?
Goal tape average so far: 1524 / 40 = 38.1 stars each.
Yay, more lava, and upside-down mushrooms.
Yeah, I'm going to have to wait here.
So, 4-1 it is! Let's do the "Magma Wave" here!
Could've skipped that horizontally moving saw as well, but I second-guessed myself there. At least that didn't result in any disasters.
Yep, we've got lava on layer 2 here. Just make sure you know where the high ground is and be patient and you should be fine.
Pop quiz: What game was that? First to answer correctly gets 3 Happy Smile points! (UPDATE: 8azaz22 got it. It's the first Breath of Fire game. Specifically, the SNES version.)
And line-guided ropes.
Yeah, I really screwed that one up... This'll hurt my average big-time. (BTW, that sound effect was from the rocket screen-clearing effect in Mario Paint.)
Decided to enter this one differently than usual.
Obviously, get off the moving platform and find higher ground/vines during high tide here.
Managed to dodge that one completely.
D'oh! So, do the bottoms of upright saws extend farther than they appear as well?
To be continued...
That was pretty well hidden. I wonder how long it would've taken me to find it if it wasn't for raocow's video...
Now we've got these balance mushrooms or whatever they're called. Ride the one on the right downwards at low tide to get a star coin.
I probably want to stomp more than one parakoopduder here this time.
No need to duck here. You'll spaz out, but won't fall (although you'll gradually be pushed to the left side of the platform).
Man, I should've just gotten off of that one earlier, when I first saw this cement ledge, since all that I got up there was a few coins.
Wow, I got kind of beat up back there, but I'm still alive, and I've reached the normal exit here.
I just want to make sure I didn't miss something that would only be visible at low tide... Huh, that's interesting how those mushroom platforms don't spawn immediately from this side.
That opens up 4-A. Now, let's go back and get 4-1's normal exit.
Well, maybe I could've max speed jumped or podoboo spin jumped onto that high ledge to save time, but whatever.
Umm... I think I just made it so that I didn't have to dodge that saw at all.
Ah, yes. The boiling cocoa stairs. Definitely a unique naturally-occurring feature that's exclusive to this area.

And, now that I've touched this rope, the glitch has ended. I could retrigger it, but I'm not going to do that. Hmm... It appears the shell is gone for good, so I guess I'm not getting the secret exit on this trip.
Yay for visible invisible blocks!
Stand on this block to stay safe during this high tide.
Wow, that's five levels to choose from! So, place your votes for either 4-2, 4-5, 4-B, 5-4, or 7-1, and we'll find out where I go next time!
Yo, dudes! Welcome back to Super Marina World! Now, let's take a look at the polls to see where I'll be heading next!
And here, the ropes spell out "MARINA", though most of these letters look rather weird.
So what you do is get this mushroom to rise up a bit, then jump off screen onto the upward-pointing pillar. Then, just jump one more time to teleport to the secret exit's room.
And, we get a bonus game.
Oh, that is just so convenient how the natural formation of these boiling cocoa stairs fits perfectly with where the platform will be at high tide here.
Whoa. I had tried pressing down to grab onto one of them at first, but I can only grab onto these ropes by pressing up, unlike vines and fences.
That was neat.
Okay, this time, let's keep heading to the right from here.

Now, see this P-switch and pipe up here? Those lead to the secret exit. However, I'm not going to break the level like this, so I'll just end the glitch. The glitch ends for real if you leave the area, or come into contact with another line-guided rope.
That unlocks 4-2. So, where should I go next? Actually, I think I'll go with 4-A right now, just because I want to.
